column1: description

IVUS imaging shows a eccentric mixed fibro-lipidic plaque in the right coronary artery, with minimal (≤25% area stenosis). Vessel demonstrates concentric lumen narrowing. Plaque morphology remains stable with no evidence of acute thrombus, intimal tear, or stent-related complications. Impression: CAD-RADS 1 disease corresponding to recent onset exertional chest discomfort. Non-obstructive atherosclerotic plaque. Recommended management includes consideration of percutaneous coronary intervention.
